  - P6
group: role-qa-engineer
persona: "QA engineer / test lead in an indie or small-team product context."

intent: |
  Move from the messy starting condition to the explicit done state for: Regression suite hardening: flaky test elimination. Done when: CI flake rate < 1% sustained for 4 weeks, every quarantined test has a triage owner + ETA, no test is muted without a tracked root-cause ticket, retry logic removed except for documented infrastructure cases, and a flake-budget policy is enforced in PR review.

scope: |
  Done when: CI flake rate < 1% sustained for 4 weeks, every quarantined test has a triage owner + ETA, no test is muted without a tracked root-cause ticket, retry logic removed except for documented infrastructure cases, and a flake-budget policy is enforced in PR review.

summary: |
  Regression suite hardening: flaky test elimination. Done when: CI flake rate < 1% sustained for 4 weeks, every quarantined test has a triage owner + ETA, no test is muted without a tracked root-cause ticket, retry logic removed except for documented infrastructure cases, and a flake-budget policy is enforced in PR review.

non_goals:
  - "Tooling holy wars — picking the stack is a side-effect, not the goal"
  - "Org-design / hiring changes outside the scope of this engagement"
  - "Speculative work without an acceptance criterion to test against"

prerequisites:
  - "Stakeholder + decision-maker named at kickoff"
  - "Access to the systems / dashboards / repos the playbook touches"
  - "Budget signed for the tooling + telemetry this playbook depends on"

success_criteria:
  - "Done-state achieved as described in the scope: Done when: CI flake rate < 1% sustained for 4 weeks, every quarantined test has a triage owner + ETA, no test is muted without a tracked root-cause ticket, retry logic removed except for documented infrastructure cases, and a flake-budget policy is enforced in PR review."
  - "Decision doc signed: continue / iterate / kill, backed by evidence."
  - "Runbook + acceptance criteria in source control, handed to on-call / next owner."
  - "All must-fix issues from Harden / Pilot closed; nice-to-fix backlog ticketed."

